<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">(paratypes). Russia. Tuva Republic</emphasis>
: Western Sayan, Kurtushibinskiy ridge, the upper Mynas river, right tributary of the Hut river, forb-grass meadow, 1080 m alt., 6 Jul 1989, D. Shaulo &amp; I. Kovaleva 4695 (NS barcode 0013098!); Mongun-Tayga region, valley of Tolayty river, yernik-sedge wetland meadow, 2500 m alt., 26 Jul 1980, M. Danilov &amp; A. Krytsin 932 (NS barcode 0013096!); the northern slope of the East Tannu-Ola ridge, the average flow of Elegest river, floodplain, No., 22 Jul 1973, V. Khanminchun &amp; V. Dyukov 2270 (NS barcode 0013095!); 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Kemerovo Oblast</emphasis>
: Tashtagol region, the village of Ust-Kabyrza 4 km above Pysas river, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="52" direction="north" minutes="48" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="52.8">52°48'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="88" direction="east" minutes="28" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="88.46667">88°28'E</geoCoordinate>
, 450 m alt., grass meadow, haymaking, 11 Sep 2000, I. M. Krasnoborov, A. I. Shmakov, D. Germann, S. Kostyukov, E. Antonuk, P. Kosachev &amp; A. Vashchenko 207 (NS barcode 0013094!); 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Krasnoyarsk Krai</emphasis>
: Abansky region, near Ustyanskoye village, the upper part of the eastern slope, upland meadow, 6 Jul 1956 T. Vagina (NS barcode 0013093!); Ermakovsky district, valley of the US river, elevation 852 m alt., 
<geoCoordinate degrees="52.2847" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="5" value="52.2847">52.2847°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="93.2517" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="5" value="93.2517">93.2517°E</geoCoordinate>
, 03 Jul 2010, I.V. Khan &amp; E.A. Balde 152 (NSK barcode 0028601!); 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Khakassia Republic</emphasis>
: Abansky ridge, near Biskamzha station, southern slope, burning, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="53.25" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="555" value="53.25">53.25N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="089.30" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="555" value="89.3">089.30E</geoCoordinate>
, 700 m alt., 4 Jun 1991, E. Ankipovich (NS barcode 0013092!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="affinities">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Affinities.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erst &amp; Luferov" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Trollius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trollius austrosibiricus" order="Ranunculales" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austrosibiricus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Trollius austrosibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. chinensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">T. chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bunge and 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. macropetalus" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="macropetalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">T. macropetalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Regel) Fr.Schmidt. It is well distinguished by simple rhizomes (rather than by the multi-headed basal part of the plant, as in 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. chinensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">T. chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. macropetalus" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="macropetalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">T. macropetalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), shorter aerial shoots, smaller flowers and shorter persistent styles (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphological comparison between Trollius austrosibiricus and related species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/18C3BFBAAD4CC4BECF0EECB50E92B5D7" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" tableUuid="18C3BFBAAD4CC4BECF0EECB50E92B5D7">1</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Trollius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trollius chinensis" order="Ranunculales" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Trollius chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an East Asian species occurring in Russia (Primorsky and Khabarovsk territories, Sakhalin), in the north and northeast of China and on the Korean peninsula (
<bibRefCitation author="Schipczinsky, NV" journalOrPublisher="Publishing House of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" pagination="42 - 53" refId="B12" refString="Schipczinsky, NV, 1937. Genus globe-flower - Trollius L. Flora of the USSR. Publishing House of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow, Leningrad 7: 42 - 53" title="Genus globe-flower - Trollius L. Flora of the USSR." volume="7" year="1937">Schipczinsky 1937</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Siplivinsky, VN" journalOrPublisher="Publishing House of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B13" refString="Siplivinsky, VN, 1972. The genus Trollius L. on the North and East of Asia. Novitates systematicae plantarum vascularium. Leningrad.9: 163-182. [In Russian with Latin description]" title="The genus Trollius L. on the North and East of Asia. Novitates systematicae plantarum vascularium. Leningrad. 9: 163 - 182. [In Russian with Latin description]" year="1972">Siplivinsky 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Doroczewska, A" journalOrPublisher="Panstwowe wydawnictwo naukowe, Warszawa" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B4" refString="Doroczewska, A, 1974. The genus Trollius L. A taxonomical study. Monographiae botanicae. Panstwowe wydawnictwo naukowe, Warszawa" title="The genus Trollius L. A taxonomical study. Monographiae botanicae." year="1974">Doroczewska 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kitagawa, M" journalOrPublisher="Gantner, Vaduz" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B8" refString="Kitagawa, M, 1979. Neo-Lineamenta Florae Manshuricae - Flora et vegetatio mundi. Gantner, Vaduz" title="Neo-Lineamenta Florae Manshuricae - Flora et vegetatio mundi." year="1979">Kitagawa 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Woroshilov, VN" journalOrPublisher="Nauka, Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B18" refString="Woroshilov, VN, 1982. Plants of the Soviet Far East. Nauka, Moscow" title="Plants of the Soviet Far East." year="1982">Woroshilov 1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Luferov, AN" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Moscow Society of Naturalists, Biological series," pageId="0" pageNumber="83" pagination="74 - 76" refId="B9" refString="Luferov, AN, 1991. New nomenclatural combinations in taxonomy of Far Eastern species of the family Ranunculaceae Juss. Bulletin of Moscow Society of Naturalists, Biological series, 96 (5): 74 - 76" title="New nomenclatural combinations in taxonomy of Far Eastern species of the family Ranunculaceae Juss." volume="96" year="1991">Luferov 1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Luferov, AN" journalOrPublisher="Turczaninowia" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" pagination="1 - 85" refId="B10" refString="Luferov, AN, 2004. A taxonomic synopsis of Ranunculaceae of the Far East of Russia. Turczaninowia 7 (1): 1 - 85" title="A taxonomic synopsis of Ranunculaceae of the Far East of Russia." volume="7" year="2004">2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
This new species is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. asiaticus" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="asiaticus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">T. asiaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. by a smaller number of sepals, longer persistent styles and petals longer than sepals (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphological comparison between Trollius austrosibiricus and related species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/18C3BFBAAD4CC4BECF0EECB50E92B5D7" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" tableUuid="18C3BFBAAD4CC4BECF0EECB50E92B5D7">1</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Trollius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trollius asiaticus" order="Ranunculales" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="asiaticus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Trollius asiaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows mainly in extra-tropical Asia (Western and Eastern Siberia, Mongolia, northeast Kazakhstan and China), as well as in the northeast of European Russia (
<bibRefCitation author="Schipczinsky, NV" journalOrPublisher="Publishing House of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" pagination="42 - 53" refId="B12" refString="Schipczinsky, NV, 1937. Genus globe-flower - Trollius L. Flora of the USSR. Publishing House of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow, Leningrad 7: 42 - 53" title="Genus globe-flower - Trollius L. Flora of the USSR." volume="7" year="1937">Schipczinsky 1937</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Siplivinsky, VN" journalOrPublisher="Publishing House of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B13" refString="Siplivinsky, VN, 1972. The genus Trollius L. on the North and East of Asia. Novitates systematicae plantarum vascularium. Leningrad.9: 163-182. [In Russian with Latin description]" title="The genus Trollius L. on the North and East of Asia. Novitates systematicae plantarum vascularium. Leningrad. 9: 163 - 182. [In Russian with Latin description]" year="1972">Siplivinsky 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Doroczewska, A" journalOrPublisher="Panstwowe wydawnictwo naukowe, Warszawa" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B4" refString="Doroczewska, A, 1974. The genus Trollius L. A taxonomical study. Monographiae botanicae. Panstwowe wydawnictwo naukowe, Warszawa" title="The genus Trollius L. A taxonomical study. Monographiae botanicae." year="1974">Doroczewska 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Borodina-Grabovskaya, AE" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B1" refString="Borodina-Grabovskaya, AE, 2001. Trollius L. In: Plantae Asiae Centralis, Vol. 12. Publ. SPKHFA, 17-21. [In Russian]" title="Trollius L. In: Plantae Asiae Centralis, Vol. 12. Publ. SPKHFA, 17 - 21. [In Russian]" year="2001">Borodina-Grabovskaya 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Friesen, NV" journalOrPublisher="Panstwowe wydawnictwo naukowe, Warszawa" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B5" refString="Friesen, NV, 2003. Trollius L. - Flora of Siberia (Vol. 6). Science Publ., Inc., Enfield and Plymouth, 98-103." title="Trollius L. - Flora of Siberia (Vol. 6). Science Publ., Inc., Enfield and Plymouth, 98 - 103." year="2003">Friesen 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
